<h1 id='consumer-experience'>Consumer Experience</h1>
<p>The Consumer Experience (CX) Standards contain requirements for the creation of implementations by both Data Recipients and Data Holders. The full list of CX Standards can be found <a href="#consumer-experience-standards">below</a></p>

<p>The CX Guidelines provide examples and recommendations for how to implement key rules and standards that relate to the consumer experience. They can be found along with additional CX commentary at:<br/></p>

<ul>
<li><a href='./pdfs/CX-Guidelines-v1.4.0.pdf'>CX Guidelines</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Additional CX commentary can be found at the <a href="https://consumerdatastandards.gov.au/workinggroups/consumer-experience/">CDR CX Stream Web Site</a>.</p>
